Springboks player Elton Jantjies signs a rugby ball for a fan after the South African Rugby team's arrival at the O.R. Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg on November 5, 2019. Guillem Sartorio / AFP JOHANNESBURG - World Cup winning Springboks flyhalf Elton Jantjies has been arrested according to reports. The 31-year-old was reportedly travelling from Dubai when he was apprehended and escorted off the plane on landing at OR Tambo Airport. He was arrested for malicious damage to airline property. READ: Honouring Siya Kolosi | Grey's main rugby field now 'Kolisi Field' Jantjies’ social media feeds appear to indicate that he and his family had travelled to Dubai for the week and were headed back to South Africa. SA rugby says they have been informed about the arrest, but await further details.